items.title: Boston City Council member arrested on fraud and theft charges
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Boston city councilor Tania Fernandes Anderson pleaded not guilty to federal fraud charges after being arrested Friday. Anderson is accused of funneling money from a staffer to whom she was related into her own pockets. (AP video: Rodrique Ngowi). Read more: https://bit.ly/3VtdQxk

items.author: Associated Press
items.content:

items.title: LIVE: South Korea’s ruling party holds an emergency meeting in parliament
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from inside South Korea's parliament as the People Power Party holds a closed-door emergency meeting.
South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol is facing possible impeachment for sending heavily armed soldiers into Seoul's streets with a declaration of martial law that reminded many of the country’s past military-backed dictatorships. Read more: https://bit.ly/3ZjOLWT

items.title: South Korean president 'truly sorry', says he won't seek to impose martial law again
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:

items.title: Pearl Harbor survivor, 100, remembers Japanese attack 83 years later
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Robert Fernandez was 17 when his U.S. Navy ship was attacked by Japanese forces at Pearl Harbor on Dec. 7, 1941, when more than 2,300 U.S. servicemen were killed. The California man, 100, is one of about 20 survivors still alive. (AP Video/Terry Chea)
